  "abstract": "The Board of Governors of the Federal Reserve System (Board) is adopting a proposal to extend for three years, without revision the Disclosure Requirements in Connection with Regulation H (Consumer Protection in Sales of Insurance) (FR H-7; OMB No. 7100-0298).",
  "action": "On July 31, 2024, the Board published a notice in the Federal Register (89 FR 61422) requesting public comment for 60 days on the extension, without revision, of the FR H-7. The comment period for this notice expired on September 30, 2024. The Board did not receive any comments. The revisions will be implemented as proposed.",
